<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd">
<task id="task_pjr_5h4_4v">
    <title>Restarting Data Collector</title>
    <taskbody>
        <context><indexterm>Data Collector<indexterm>restarting</indexterm></indexterm>You can
            restart <ph
                conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/> to
            apply changes to the <ph
                conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/>
            configuration file, environment configuration file, or user logins. During the restart
            process, <ph
                conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"/>
            shuts down and then automatically restarts.<note>If you installed <ph
                    conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                /> through Cloudera Manager, you must use Cloudera Manager to restart <ph
                    conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/pName-long"
                />. For information about how to restart a service through Cloudera Manager, see the
                Cloudera documentation.</note></context>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click <menucascade>
                        <uicontrol>Administration</uicontrol>
                        <uicontrol>Restart</uicontrol>
                    </menucascade>.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>When a confirmation dialog box appears, click <uicontrol>Yes</uicontrol>.
                </cmd>
                <info> The restart process can take a few moments to complete. Refresh the browser
                    to log in again.</info>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
